  "text": "Next, we induced pre-TCR signaling in RAG-1-deficient mice by injecting anti-CD3⑀ mAb. Thymocytes were harvested prior to CD25 down-regulation and cycling (6 hours) and when a significant fraction of RAG-1-deficient thymocytes are cycling (24 hours). [CITATION_1] Upon the induction of pre-TCR signaling total as well as active ␤-catenin levels did not increase, strongly suggesting that ␤-catenin was not stabilized by pre-TCR signaling ( Figure 5C ). Rather, pre-TCR limited the availability of active ␤-catenin. Similar to total or active ␤-catenin, ␥-catenin (plakoglobin) also did not increase following pre-TCR signaling ( Figure 5C ).",
